ws.rocket.path.annotation

Annotation Type TreeNode


  • @Documented
@Retention(value=RUNTIME)
@Target(value=TYPE)
public @interface TreeNode
    Annotation used on TreeNode values (classes) for describing the node to be constructed where the annotated value object will belong to. Since the node value object is known (instance of the annotated class), this annotation describes the key (reference to a key object) and the possible child nodes (references to their value objects).

    For both node key and child node values it is possible to use either reference by bean name or reference by type. When key attributes are omitted, the tree node key will be null. When children attributes are omitted, the constructed tree node will not have any children.

    See Also:
    TreeNode

      • keyType

        public abstract java.lang.Class<?> keyType
        Reference to node key object by bean type. This value is used when key() is empty and keyType != Object.class. When CDI cannot resolve the type to exactly one bean, tree construction will fail.
        Returns:
        The CDI bean type for the node key object.
        Default:
        java.lang.Object.class

      • keyName

        public abstract java.lang.String keyName
        Reference to node key object by CDI bean name. This value is used when key() is empty, keyType() == Object.class, and the value of this attribute is not empty.
        Returns:
        The CDI bean name for the node key object.
        Default:
        ""

        Returns:

        {}
